      "description": "The ice cream cone / one-scoop graph $(2,1,1)$: 3 vertices, 4 edges, $L=2$, 3 external legs. Two trivalent vertices joined by a single edge, a chain of length 2, and a single edge. Graph polynomials $U_{(2,1,1)}, V_{(2,1,1);D}$ given in e:UVF112. In $D=2$ the cohomology $H^2(X_{(2,1,1);2};\\mathbb{Q})$ is pure Tate of rank 4; the variation of mixed Hodge structure on the pencil is built from two order-1 local systems coming from double covers of $\\mathbb{P}^1 = $ pairs of copies of the massive one-loop bubble $L_{(1,1);2}$. The order-2 Liouvillian Picard-Fuchs operator $L_{(2,1,1);2}$ equals the direct sum of these two bubble operators up to an explicit scaling factor $\\sqrt{((m_1+m_2)^2 - t p_2^2)((m_1-m_2)^2 - t p_2^2)}$.",
